quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  88,19,"And at the mountains, how they are rooted (and fixed firm)?"
  88,20,"And at the earth, how it is outspread?"
  88,21,"So remind them (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) - you are only one who reminds."
  89,16,"But when He tries him by straitening his means of life, he says: "
  89,17,"Nay! But you treat not the orphans with kindness and generosity (i.e. you neither treat them well, nor give them their exact right of inheritance)!"
  89,18,"And urge not one another on the feeding of Al-Miskîn (the poor)!"
  90,10,"And shown him the two ways (good and evil)?"
  90,11,"But he has not attempted to pass on the path that is steep (i.e. the path which will lead to goodness and success)."
  90,12,"And what will make you know the path that is steep?"
  91,7,"By Nafs (Adam or a person or a soul), and Him Who perfected him in proportion;"
  91,8,"Then He showed him what is wrong for him and what is right for him."
  91,9,"Indeed he succeeds who purifies his ownself (i.e. obeys and performs all that Allâh ordered, by following the true Faith of Islâmic Monotheism and by doing righteous good deeds)."
  92,4,"Certainly, your efforts and deeds are diverse (different in aims and purposes);"
  92,5,"As for him who gives (in charity) and keeps his duty to Allâh and fears Him,"
  92,6,"And believes in Al-Husnâ.{1}",footnotes:1:{92:6}
  93,1,"By the forenoon (after sunrise).{1}",footnotes:1:{93:1}
  93,2,"By the night when it darkens (and stand still)."
  93,3,"Your Lord (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) has neither forsaken you nor hates you."